<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF-Halfway Hotel,0110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Closed Hotel To Be Used As Halfway House</HEAD>
<DATELINE>McKEESPORT, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A closed Sheraton hotel in this
Pittsburgh suburb will be converted into a halfway house for
federal prisoners under a prison warden's plan.
   The federal Bureau of Prisons has approved the plan, Butler
County Warden Charles Fenton said recently.
   Fenton said he will have 45 days to open the center at the
four-story, 100-room former Sheraton Inn after he signs a federal
contract, which has been mailed to him.
   Under Fenton's proposal, the halfway house would hold up to 50
non-violent prisoners. Butler County would be paid a fee for each
prisoner.
</TEXT>
