<1ST_LINE>r a BC-BRF--Delta-Fatality     09-11 0150</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-BRF--Delta-Fatality,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fourteenth Victim in Delta Crash Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 64-year-old man died Sunday morning from
injuries suffered in the crash of Delta Flight 1141 last month,
bringing the death toll to 14, officials said.
   Edmond Fadal, one of two severely burned victims from the Aug.
31 crash, died at 1:43 a.m., said Cindy Gambala of the Dallas
County medical examiner's office.
   Fadal of Waco, Texas, had suffered from third-degree burns over
60 percent of his body and from smoke inhalation, officials said.
His wife, 65-year-old Marian, died in the crash.
   The 15-year-old Boeing 727 crashed at Dallas-Fort Worth
International Airport seconds after takeoff. The three-man cockpit
crew and 94 others survived.
   The National Transportation Safety Board is investigating the
cause of the crash. NTSB officials said their inquiry is focusing
on possible problems with the jet's wing flaps and its three Pratt
& Whitney JT8D engines.
