<TEXT>
   A crowded passenger bus slammed into a
stalled cement truck on a coastal highway, killing 20 and injuring
at least 20 others, police said.
   The crash occurred before dawn Saturday as the bus, carrying 60
passengers to a Pacific beach, rounded a curve and struck the
truck, which was pulled to the side of the highway but was not
