former fiancee to see a movie Aug. 14 and set off the blast just
before the end, the paper said. The couple and eight other people
were killed, and 27 people were injured. More than 1,000 people
were in the theater, it said.
   The newspaper did not say why it waited so long to report the
explosion. None of China's other official publications reported it.
