<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--BusCrash     09-11 0179</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Bus Crash,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bus Crashes After Driver Dies at the Wheel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>McKENNEY, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Greyhound bus driver collapsed and died
at the wheel, sending his bus crashing into several trees on a
freeway median while a passenger tried to bring it under control.
Three people were injured.
   James Maxwell, 60, collapsed with an apparent heart attack about
11 a.m. Friday near this town 45 miles south of Richmond, said Liz
Hale, a spokesman for Greyhound-Trailways Lines in Dallas.
   Passenger Richard Lee Stallings of Wake Forest, N.C., saw
Maxwell collapse and grabbed the steering wheel while trying to
remove the driver from his seat, said trooper P.E. Israel of the
Virginia State Police.
   The northbound bus began to veer into southbound lanes of
Interstate 85, and Stallings was unable to keep the bus on the
road, Israel said. But he did keep the bus from crashing into
oncoming traffic or overturning.
   The bus hit several trees in the median before stopping. Three
of the 21 passengers were injured, including one woman who was in
stable condition Sunday.
</TEXT>
