<HEAD>7 Jailed For Allegedly Taking Hostages To Dig Pit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WOODLAND PARK, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Seven campers armed with four
shotguns, an automatic rifle and several handguns allegedly took
three people captive and forced them to dig a pit for a pig roast,
authorities said.
   The seven men were arrested by 14 officers from several law
enforcement agencies who crept up to the campsite in the mountains
north of here and surrounded it Saturday, said Undersheriff Donald
Christensen.
