stumbled onto the campsite and didn't know their captors,
Christensen said.
   The hostages may have been taken as early as Friday evening. The
sheriff's office said it got a tip Saturday morning, and verified
it by flying over the area.
   Christensen said a dead pig was left at the site, but wasn't
roasted.
