<DOCNO> AP880911-0081 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-09-11-88 2156EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a AM-DeltaCrash-Fatality     09-11 0205</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Delta Crash-Fatality,0210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>14th Fatality Sustained Burns Trying to Rescue His Wife</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who on Sunday became the 14th fatality of
the Delta Flight 1141 wreck died of injuries sustained when he
returned to the airplane in a futile attempt to save his wife,
friends said.
   Edmond Fadal, 64, of Waco died early Sunday at Parkland Memorial
Hospital, where he had been listed in critical condition since the
Aug. 31 crash of the Boeing 727 at Dallas-Fort Worth International
Airport.
   His wife Marian, 65, died in the crash along with 12 others.
Ninety-four passengers and crew members survived the accident.
   Jean and Frank Nix, also of Waco, had joined the Fadals on the
Delta flight for a trip to Lake Tahoe.
   Mrs. Nix, 54, told The Associated Press Sunday that three of
them escaped from the jet wreckage without severe injuries, but
Fadal returned to the plane for his wife.
   ``The plane broke open right in front of us,'' Mrs. Nix
recalled. ``We all unbuckled our seat belts and tried to run out.
... We never looked back.''
   But when the Nixes and Edmond Fadal noticed Marian Fadal was not
with them, Fadal ran back to the wreckage, they said.
</TEXT>
